.TH "task_is_descendant" 9 "task_is_descendant" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
task_is_descendant \- walk up a process family tree looking for a match
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" task_is_descendant
.BI "(struct task_struct *parent "  ","
.BI "struct task_struct *child "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
the process to compare against while walking up from child
.IP "child" 12
the process to start from while looking upwards for parent
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 1 if child is a descendant of parent, 0 if not.
